com.inqwell.any.io.sql

Class SqlStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractComposite
      • com.inqwell.any.AbstractMap
        • com.inqwell.any.PropertyAccessMap
          • com.inqwell.any.io.sql.SqlStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, Composite, PhysicalIO, Map, Serializable, Cloneable

    public class SqlStream
extends PropertyAccessMap
implements PhysicalIO, Cloneable
    Stream-style SQL i/o. This class supports I/O to an sql source/sink such that it appears as a stream would, appending records as they are written and returning them successively as they are read.

      • delete

        public boolean delete(Map outputItem,
                      Transaction t)
               throws AnyException
        Delete the given item using the given key.

        Implemented to run the deleteSql statement, parameterised with the given value. If the prepared or stproc properties are set then the supplied Map must carry ordering information.

        The deleteSql may perform any operation, whether related or not to any previous reads or writes and may delete zero, one or many items.

        Specified by:
        delete in interface PhysicalIO
        Returns:
        true if deleted successfully.
        Throws:
        AnyException - if an exception is reported by the physical medium.
